args:
Xander is quite excited about Dragonyule,
but his enthusiasm amounts to little, so the
prince appoints Cleo and Nefaria to help out.
Together, the three dress like Saint Starfall
and are dispatched to eliminate fiends
threatening the people's holiday cheer.
Whoa, so THIS is a Yuletree?\nIt's amazing!
I'm glad we were able to put it up without\nany problems.
Listen up, everyone! On Dragonyule,\nI'm planning to invite all the villagers\nto the castle for a big party.
However, it's possible fiends could attack\nagain, so we can't let our guard down.
That being said, let's make sure it's a\nwonderful Dragonyule celebration!
Hello, Xander. Care to help out?
Hmph! I'd typically never permit the affront\nof a vassal making demands of his king.\nHowever...
Who claims the mantle of kingship?\nThe rightful lord of this castle remains\n{player_name}.
Ha HA! I will not stand for such cheek\nwhen it comes from the lips of a\nshamefully deposed ruler.
I am not the only former monarch here,\nXander.
Yet I am the king and ruler of this castle!\nI speak it thus, and thus it is so!
Have you not forgotten the most\nindispensable part of Dragonyule?
If I have, I'm sure you're going to tell me\nall about it, aren't you?

Ha HA! So true. After all, one can hardly
speak on matters of Dragonyule without
ALSO mentioning that jolly bringer of good
tidings, Saint Starfall!
Ah, right. You wouldn't know about\nhim either...
To commemorate Ilia's birth, a great\nmany people gave the newborn's\nfamily celebratory gifts.

Among those people was a person
who did not meet the infant goddess,
but instead placed their gift on a tree
in front of her home before departing.

According to stories handed down
over the long years, this person was
the incarnation of the Holywyrm
Elysium.

Three centuries later, the benevolent
king of a certain land took it upon
himself to mimic the particulars of
this tale.

He adorned himself with reindeer
horns and dressed like Elysium, then
traveled his kingdom placing gifts
beneath the eaves of homes.
His people delighted in these gifts,\nand carried on the practice down\nthrough the generations.
This gift-giver is now known as the\nsymbol of Dragonyule, Saint Starfall.
He was a great king of deep mercy.\nRather like me, wouldn't you say?
Indeed! Thusly shall I take it upon myself\nto bear the heavy crown of Saint Starfall!
I shall set about my preparations with all\nhaste. Come, lackies! Attend your regent!
Maybe the great and benevolent regent\nshould zip his lip for a hot second!
Surely you doubt his plan as much as\nI do, {player_name}?
Yes, but I can't really fault his enthusiasm.\nMaybe we could let him try it and see\nhow it goes?
Oh, come on! Don't be a chowderhead!
The thought of this knave playing at\nSaint Starfall is an ill one indeed.
Xander?! What in the world is that statue?!
It is a carving modeled on my own gallant\nvisage! What say you? Inspiring, is it not?
Forget bein' inspired—the hell are ya\nDOIN' with the thing?!
Why, I'm gifting it to the people, of course.
I fear you're grossly overestimating their\nneed for such a present.
Hang on. That thing can't be cheap—\nespecially considerin' it's a custom job.\nDon't tell me ya PAID for it?!
Worry not! I used the Dragonyule funds\ngiven to me by {player_name}.
He's ruined Dragonyule already?\nI'm almost impressed.
Why the dumbstruck faces, my vassals?!\nGaze instead upon the resplendent visage\nof this statue and be re-invigorated!
Fie, but I can abide this idiocy no longer!\nYou, sirrah, must cast your eye inward\nand take a hard look at yourself!

Guiding one's people to happiness!
Bringing smiles to the countenances
of all! THESE are the actions of
Saint Starfall—and of a king.

And yet, here you stand, bold as brass
and more fool than the basest village oaf,
having robbed the people of all cheer!
Such actions cannot be forgiven!
Wh-what did you just say to me?!
Stop flapping your gums for one moment\nand listen to me.
What Nefaria says is right—however,\nnothing will come from unfocused anger.
And though it pains me to say this,\nI know Xander to be quite capable\nwhen he puts his mind to something.
Quite so and hear hear! This woman is—

BUT! You're still acting like a fool.
So if you really want to be a hero
of the people, figure out a solution
to this mess.
Urk! H-how can a mere scullery maid\nhave such a fearsome presence?!
Hmm... Maybe things can work out with\nthis group after all.
Well, Nefaria is calm and collected,\nwhile Xander is a man who acts first\nand asks questions... Never, actually.

But somehow, Cleo seems to be able to
keep both of them under control—and
I think the three of them together are
going to be perfect.
I do mean it. I want the three of you to\nwork together and EACH be Saint Starfall.
Have you forgotten that I am sylvan?!
That's even better! You'll learn all\nabout Dragonyule and make some\ngreat memories along the way.

An excellent plan! Now you two will know
the sacrifice of playing Saint Starfall—
and of course, come to appreciate me
all the more in the process.
I would settle for merely learning that you\nare not the hapless rapscallion you so\nclearly appear to be.
Enough, both of you! Uuurgh...\nThis is already turning my stomach.
...Right then. Xander said something about\nSaint Starfall wearing a red outfit.
I tried to make something appropriate,\nbut is this good enough?
Can I truly wear this and deliver gifts to\neveryone? Even {player_name}?
Or am I just a foolish sylvan for even\nharboring such a thought?
Cleo, could I have a momen—whoa.
ACK! Th-this it's not what it looks like,\n{player_name}!
Er, so you're NOT dressed up in a\nSaint Starfall outfit?
That is what it was SUPPOSED to be,\nbut I fear I may have gotten it wrong.
There's no right or wrong to it, really.
And yet, Dragonyule is a human festival.
Not here, it isn't. I want everyone in the\ncastle to celebrate this day, no matter\nwhat their heritage may be.
I'm not concerned with form or tradition.\nWhat's most important is that everyone\nenjoys themselves.
And yet, is it truly acceptable for me,\na sylvan, to do so?
Anyways, I'm going to get going.\nI'm trusting you with this, Cleo!
Very well. It seems I have a great deal\nof work ahead of me...
Ha HA! This outfit is splendid!\nSimply splendid!
Was it not arduous to prepare\nthese garments for us, Cleo?
Then thanks to your efforts, we shall enjoy\na festive Dragonyule season as well.
I am most grateful, Saint Starfall Cleo.
Oh man, this ain't good.\nWe got fiends incoming!
Ha HA! In that case, Saint Starfall now\ndeparts for the brave front of gift-giving!
We're going out in THESE outfits?!
The queen over there said it herself:\nIt is a monarch's duty to bring\nhappiness to the people.
If we lead the way and enjoy ourselves,\nthe rabble will simply fall in line!
Now then! If you are attendants who would\nserve their king, then obey a king's will!\nFollow behind me at once!
I suppose the prince DID say he wanted\nto see me enjoy myself...
So I am going to do just that—AND make\nsure everyone else does, too!
I am Saint Starfall, guided by the prince!\nI fight to bring happiness to all!
